{
  "texts": [
    "6 and 7 empirically verify and generalize the advantages expected from the theory and show that prospective configuration yields more accurate error allocation and less erratic weight modifica tion, respectively.",
    "Inspired by these advantages, we show empirically that prospective configuration indeed handles various learning problems that bio logical systems would face better than backpropagation.",
    "Because the field of machine learning has developed effective benchmarks for testing learning performance, we use variants of classic machine 1 showing changes in the correct and incorrect output neurons during training ('Iteration') trained with both learning rules.",
    "Here, learning with prospective configuration (purple solid vector) aligns better with the target (red vector) than learning with backpropagation (purple dashed vector).",
    "b, Interference can be quantified by 'target alignment', the cosine similarity of the direction of the target (red vector) and the direction of learning (purple vector)."
  ]
}